stylometry: Standard deviation is important because it allows you to see the variability from the mean. Without standard deviation, you may not chose the best result. Often times people look at what will get them the highest profit. This is not always the case because there is some risk with choices. Say you have the choice between two stocks. Stock A has a return of 10% and has a standard deviation of 20. Stock B has a return of 12% and has a standard deviation of 30. Many people would chose B because it gives you a greater return but it is riskier. The standard deviation is higher and there is more variability from the mean. People who look at the standard deviation might not think the 2% difference is worth going for B when the standard deviation of A is smaller.
